WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:04.580
Chapter 22 of Proverbs, King James Version.

00:04.900 --> 00:07.460
This LibriVox recording is in the public domain.

00:08.060 --> 00:09.700
Recording by Michael Packard.

00:10.800 --> 00:14.460
A good name is rather to be chosen than great riches,

00:15.320 --> 00:18.700
And loving favor rather than silver and gold.

00:20.100 --> 00:25.060
The rich and poor meet together, The Lord is the maker of them all.

00:25.860 --> 00:30.820
A prudent man foreseeeth the evil, And hideeth himself,

00:31.720 --> 00:34.100
But the simple pass on and are punished.

00:35.120 --> 00:39.700
By humility and the fear of the Lord Are riches and honor and life.

00:41.860 --> 00:45.440
Thorns and snares are in the way of the froward,

00:46.400 --> 00:50.260
He that doth keep his soul shall be far from them.

00:52.020 --> 00:58.020
Train up a child in the way he should go, And when he is old he will not depart from it.

00:59.860 --> 01:05.520
The rich ruleth over the poor, And the borrower is servant to the lender.

01:07.580 --> 01:13.100
He that soweth iniquity shall reap vanity, And the rod of his anger shall fail.

01:14.540 --> 01:20.240
He that hath a bountiful eye shall be blessed, For he giveth of his bread to the poor,

01:22.520 --> 01:26.180
Cast out the scornor, and contention shall go out,

01:26.320 --> 01:28.700
Yea strife and reproach shall cease.

01:29.940 --> 01:35.360
He that loveth pureness of heart, For the grace of his lips the king shall be his friend.

01:37.160 --> 01:43.280
The eyes of the Lord preserve knowledge, And he overthroweth the words of the transgressor.

01:44.720 --> 01:50.080
The slothful man saith, There is a lion without, I shall be slain in the streets.

01:50.700 --> 01:57.700
The mouth of strange women is a deep pit, He that is abhorred of the Lord shall fall therein.

02:00.040 --> 02:05.840
Foolishness is bound in the heart of a child, But the rod of correction shall drive it far from him.

02:07.800 --> 02:10.800
He that oppresseth the poor to increase his riches,

02:11.260 --> 02:15.040
And he that giveth to the rich shall surely come to want.

02:16.400 --> 02:23.240
Bow down thine ear, and hear the words of the wise, And apply thine heart unto my knowledge.

02:24.060 --> 02:27.140
For it is a pleasant thing if thou keep them within thee,

02:27.600 --> 02:32.840
They shall withal be fitted in thy lips, That thy trust may be in the Lord.

02:33.260 --> 02:36.020
I have made known to thee this day even to thee.

02:36.620 --> 02:40.360
Have not I written to thee excellent things in counsels and knowledge,

02:40.920 --> 02:44.540
That I might make thee know the certainty of the words of truth?

02:44.540 --> 02:49.260
That thou mightest answer the words of truth to them that send unto thee.

02:51.260 --> 02:56.580
Rob not the poor, because he is poor, Neither oppress the afflicted in the gate,

02:56.860 --> 03:02.500
For the Lord will plead their cause, And spoil the soul of those that spoil them.

03:04.400 --> 03:09.420
Make no friendship with an angry man, And with a furious man thou shalt not go,

03:10.160 --> 03:13.920
Lest thou learn his ways, and get a snare to thy soul.

03:13.920 --> 03:20.360
Be not thou one of them that strike hands, Or of them that are sureties for debts.

03:21.000 --> 03:25.860
If thou hast nothing to pay, why should he take away thy bed from under thee?

03:26.860 --> 03:30.500
Remove not the ancient landmark which thy fathers have set.

03:31.860 --> 03:36.520
Seest thou a man diligent in his business? He shall stand before kings,

03:36.700 --> 03:39.160
He shall not stand before mean men.

